l/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Burn the Witch!</span><br>  Posts: 1495<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 8:43:27 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/ladun.jpg width=67 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> I'd like to pull several separate threads into one.  We have a couple of issues that could use some discussion.<br>
<br>
1. Cazic Thule.  He's a L57+ encounter in a zone made for mostly 46-54's.  It's questionable whether there's more than 2 groups on server that can even take him out.<br>
<br>
Question 1: Should CT still be considered a part of the regular Fear raid &amp; Scheduled?<br>
<br>
*Yes, only a scheduled fear raid should be allowed to kill him.<br>
*Yes, but another group can come in as long as they have the permission of the scheduled raiders.<br>
*No, the new CT is in a separate league from the traditional Fear raid, and should be treated separately.<br>
*Your own opinion.<br>
<br>
2. Hate.  There's a 2nd floor that is in some ways like PoG but also dropping things for rangers/pallies/druids.  Mobs are slightly higher level, pathing seems really lousy.  The time involved in clearing the main floor, then the second will likely be considerable.  Innoruuk seems to be similar to CT in some respects, although easier.  <br>
<br>
Q2: Should the second floor of hate remain tied to scheduled raids of the first floor? (This includes Innoruuk)<br>
<br>
*Yes, only people with a scheduled regular hate raid should be able to raid the 2nd floor.<br>
*Yes, but a second group may cooperatively work on the separate floors, provided they work things out with the group that scheduled the raid.<br>
*No, the second floor should be considerered a new zone, and treated as such.<br>
<br>
I need to know how people feel.  This isn't a voting thread, but if changes need to be made to the reservation rules because of the new gods/areas, I need to know what people want.  Feel free to deviate from the cookie cutter responses I've given already, or to even add your own commentary. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune2.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udexn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dexn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 376<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 8:56:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> I've heard more about Fear than I have about Hate. So, for not, I'll only give my opinion on Fear.<br>
<br>
Since the gods are currently still on a weekly spawn rate, the fairest way to do it, would be to break out another reservation board just for them. Even if it's only two groups now, soon enough (several months) there will be more that can do them. <br>
<br>
Short of a separate reservation, just work it out with the existing raids.  Personally, this can get unfair, because soon enough more people will be able to do the gods, and doubtless we'll see rants about the various strongest guilds crossing paths somewhere. But, let's hope not.<br>
<br>
Sylvaen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 2118<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 9:13:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> 1) *Yes, but another group can come in as long as they have the permission of the scheduled raiders.<br>
<br>
I don't think another scheduling system for the gods should be used just yet until it is obvious the level 60 guilds can't work together.  That just creates more layers of stuff to deal with.  They have to talk to the raid leaders anyway in order to set up times...so I don't see the problem in them asking the raid leaders if they can go after ct.  I'm only for this if obtaining permission is from ALL raid leaders until patch day or within one week whichever occurs first.<br>
<br>
2) *Yes, only people with a scheduled regular hate raid should be able to raid the 2nd floor. <br>
<br>
My main concerned about the number of linkdeaths and lag if we have two raids going on.  You would have to coordinate start times as well as portups etc who has priority?  If someone that can't handle the second floor wipes out, they may make it painful for the first floor raid in bugging them to help.  I just can see this as a mess.  If L/D and lag were fixed, I probably could go along with separate raids even though they would be more of a pain to set up. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaphdia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saphdia</A> at: 3/20/01 12:36:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeyanaubaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyan Aubaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 10:17:31 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> let's look at the different options :<br>
1) set different shedules<br>
not appliable imo, agroing CT agroes the whole zone, killing golems triggers DTs, you need to clear a part of the 1st floor to get to the 2nd, lag would be TERRIBLE...<br>
<br>
2) Allowing a raid to zone in if they have the permission of another raid<br>
I strongly disagree with this, it would lead to a lot of abuses, with guilds having a plane reserved for a day, and being able to go in any other day.<br>
The rule is that ANY guild/indy can only lead ONE raid per plane for every 2 week period.<br>
<br>
3) not changing anything<br>
It's the best solution for now in my opinion, CT and Inny are tough, but far from impossible to kill for a high level raid with enough ressources. the old CT and inny were not really any easier way back when we killed them for the first time, and slowly they've been easier and easier, the same thing will happen for the boosted versions.<br>
If you plan on killing a god, lead a raid going for him.<br>
If you're planning on killing a god or going to the top floors of hate, either clear the zone yourself, or make a joint raid with another guild.<br>
<br>
Making a joint raid would not stop you from doing anything you want in the plane, whether you want to only kill the god, or only go up in hate, you have a deal with the other guild so it's only a problem between you and them. You can help them, or only zone in when it's cleared enough for you not to be on their way...<br>
AND it would ensure than noone can lead several raids to a certain plane in the 2 week period.<br>
<br>
Otherwise soon you will see a guild raid a plane one day, ask the permission to kill draco the naxt day, then zone in to clear CT the 3rd day, or spend the whole week up in hate.<br>
<br>
In other words, no need to change the rules for that, since everyone can raid the different planes as they want and still follow the rules current rules.<br>
<br>
<br>
On a side note, this discussion shows what SR and friends did was not clearly a good thing, or we wouldnt be talking about it (NOT a rant, just saying that this specific example shows not everyone on the server thinks zoning in in between raids is a good thing, my rant is in the rant forum, this is NOT one) <p><b>Keyan Aubaine</b> 51 Shadowknight<br>
<b>Dynin Vifargent</b> RIP<br>
Part-time Hell-raiser</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uloven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Loven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 10:18:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> I'd vote for :<br>
<br>
*Yes, but another group can come in as long as they have the permission of the scheduled raiders.<br>
<br>
<br>
On both Hate and Fear.  All that needs to be done is the guild that's hosting the raid, if they know that CT/Inny is up, can account for this by having an &quot;extension&quot; in their signup list.  By this I mean that in their &quot;raid signup thread&quot; they can have a message saying that when they reach CT/Inny/Draco/2nd Floor Hate/etc they will bring up &quot;x&quot; number more ppl to deal with it.  They can even have in that same thread a seperate sign up for ppl who just want to do those parts.<br>
<br>
My $0.02 <br>
 <p>Loven Laviedemer <BR>
Lvl 51 Deepwater Knight <BR>
Ethos <BR>
Brell Serilis</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrimhoff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brimhoff</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 10:24:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> Question 1--*Your own opinion.<br>
If a guild that can take Cazic down wants to do so after someone elses raid is over they should feel free to do so as long as no other guild that is capable of taking Cazic down has a raid scheduled before the next patch. <br>
Example: Guild A has Fear on Saturday but are not capable of taking Cazic down.  Guild B who is capable of taking Cazic down has Fear reserved on Tuesday.  Guild C also capable of taking Cazic down should not go into Fear after Guild A is done and kill Cazic because the next scheduled patch is on Wednesday and that would leave him down for Guild B who could have taken him down.  If all the scheduled raids though before the next patch were all by guilds incapable of taking cazic down Guild C should feel free to go in after someone elses raid is over and kill Cazic.  Not many guilds can take Cazic down maybe 2 to 4 on this server right now (?) so let them work it out amongst themselves but I think people are over-reacting about what happened as being FFA.  The game constantly changes so the old rules regarding Cazic and scheduled raids no longer apply.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Question 2--*Yes, only people with a scheduled regular hate raid should be able to raid the 2nd floor. Anything less would interfere with someone elses raid.<br>
<br>
 <p>Brimhoff
54th Cavalier
<Harpers></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukeyanaubaine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Keyan Aubaine</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 90<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 10:32:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> Just something i forgot to add, if you are afraid to see CT or Inny go to waste, dont forget zoning in and killing him right before a server downtime IS allowed, and if you want to form a raid to kill him whan this happens, by all means do it.<br>
