Again, if you want to go without clearing everything, it IS possible already by accepting to do a joint raid and split the zone with the other raid. <p><b>Keyan Aubaine</b> 51 Shadowknight<br>
<b>Dynin Vifargent</b> RIP<br>
Part-time Hell-raiser</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujontann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jontann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 207<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 10:34:35 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/jontanneq/JonIcon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> On both issues it should really come down to in-game cooperation.  People should work together and see if there's a way that we can allow folks to smack down Inny and CT (or &lt;insert your boss MOB here&gt;) w/o stepping on the toes of a raid that's primarily interested in the &quot;traditional&quot; armor dropping MOBs.  <br>
<br>
I don't think there's a set line you can draw because of the varying capabilities of various guilds / raids.  For instance, last night KR did Hate.  We broke in at the portal (for chuckles and grins) and cleared the first floor in just a shade over 4 hours.  We then spent a couple of hours pulling stuff on the second floor just to try the new MOBs on for size (talk about crappy loot upstairs, BTW, unless you like junk AC 10 robes and FS.)  I know, based on past experience, that not every raid is going to have the time and / or resources to even clear to the second floor before the raid starts to peter out.  Some are, though.  If someone had approached us about wanting to take a crack at Inny, we probably would have done what we could to accomodate them without short-changing our own raid.  We had a great crew up with us last night, but there's no way we could have made a serious run at Inny.  Well, had we cleared to him we may have tried it on a lark to see how fast we could all get killed. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Personally, I'd rather see the big guys go down and have someone benefit from them than have them go to waste.<br>
