<p ALIGN=CENTER>
<A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/brell/players.cgi?view=0286">Jontann Bladefury</A> -- Level 55 Myrmidon<br></font>
<i><A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/bknightsreknown>Guild Leader -- Knights Reknown</A></i><br>
<i>Brell Serilis</i></b><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 433<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 10:56:36 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959015.jpg width = 135 height = 184></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> From what I've seen of Fear, there's all of 3 guilds that have a shot of killing Cazic.  As such, I believe they should work it out among themselves how and when they want to kill him.  As long as they don't interfere with regular raids there shouldn't be a problem.<br>
<br>
With hate, I haven't been yet, so no comment.<br>
<br>
Kalli Kamerov<br>
54th Enchantress<br>
Poison Arrow. <p><img src="http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959014.jpg"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulillianasweetleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lilliana Sweetleaf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 11:15:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> The thing is here that &quot;bringing up x new people to kill a God&quot; is not going to work here.  Lets say you have your average raid of what, 30, and you add 15 people to have 45.  These people vary in level from 46 to 56.  Guess what?  Cazic is going to break out the ol' KY jelly and go to town.  The name may be the same, but this guy is meaner than people are grasping.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, respect for the night's raid is very important as well.  I dont think a reservation board would work simply for the inability to predict the duration of a raid.  Some raids have been known to go on 8 hours or more...I dont think that many people are going to feel up for cazic at 5am.  In game talking is the key here.<br>
<br>
Lilliana Sweetleaf<br>
57 Preserver<br>
Enshadowed <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udauros.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dauros</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 11:16:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> Again,<br>
<br>
-This had better not lead to people hitting at CT or Inny while other mobs are up.  Blazing a path to the gods with reckless abandonment should not happen.  <br>
<br>
-Fighting repops to kill a god should not happen for fear of ruining another person's raid either.<br>
<br>
-Getting consent from the current raid should occur.<br>
<br>
-Getting consent from the next day's raid should occur as well, they may still want to give it a shot in hopes that they may kill the god, everyone deserves a fighting chance at the god, especially since they went through the whole reservation, two weeks in advace, board camping and all.<br>
<br>
This would be fair in my opinion, anything short of this is a direct assualt on our current raiding system. <p>Dauros 55th Enchanter of Ethos<BR>
Taeolin Retired Druid of Brell</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utatterdmalion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tatter DMalion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 11:22:27 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> For me, don't change one thing.  In the past, calls for reinforcements have gone out to help with CT and Inny.  What is the big difference now?  Only thing I see is that you need higher level folks as your reinforcement.<br>
<br>
I disagree with handing over a zone upon clearing it to another guild between raids.  That will eventually start more grief than it will solve.  Just watch for the rants, I smell them coming.<br>
<br>
And folks wonder why there is all this talk about this uberguild and that uberguild?  We are already talking about how we see a few guild capable of taking CT or Inny when in fact most of these guilds still gather assistance from other guilds.  Some folks can see this as talk of ownership if they want to.<br>
<br>
I don't think we should allow a raid to turn over the zone to another group for the express interest of boss killing.  The folks that have the raid should either call it or get reinforcements.  If they can't get the reinforcement, then pass CT or Inny to the next raid.  I think this attitude of worrying about a mob &quot;going to waste&quot; is really kind of funny.  It's going to happen with a reservation system in place.<br>
<br>
If you want the boss, schedule a raid.  If you worry about drops going to waste, lead the early portion for newbies and then bring in the big guns for the boss.  Just make sure you let the newbies know they will not get to help with the boss and not get a share of it's loot.  I think this is a better solution.<br>
<br>
