Question 1: At the current point, no, CT shouldn't be scheduled, nor tied to existing Fear reservations.  What we have now is a completely different encounter.  It just happens to be in an already reserved zone, with the same name as a mob that existed before.<br>
<br>
Imagine this.  FG reservervations are only once per day, and are perma booked.  None of the guilds killing FG's are capable of killing Nagafen at the end.  There is a guild that is capable of killing Nagafen, but is only allowed to do him if they compete with the lower guilds &amp; reserve FG's too.<br>
<br>
Fear is a 46-low 50's zone.  CT is a L57+ encounter.  They are separate encounters, that just happen to be in the same zone.  This is very much like FG's &amp; Naggy are.  Do we have a rule that Naggy can only be killed by the group that has FG's reserved?  No.  They're separate encounters, of much different difficulty, and are on different spawn timers.  This is how Fear is now.<br>
<br>
On Brell, with new mobs, we don't setup a rotation list until a mob has been killed a few times.  There wasn't a trak rotation until he'd been downed several times.<br>
<br>
As long as a CT killing raid doesn't kill repops, or doesn't interfere with existing scheduled Fear raids, I have no problems with a group going in after another raid solely to kill CT.  The 2 or 3 guilds that could possibly muster a force required to kill CT have the ability to cooperate up until the point where a rotation of some sort can be set up.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, it's harder in Hate.  We don't know how difficult it is to have separate raids running on the 2nd floor.  In Fear, regular raids can clear right up to CT.  A CT raid just has to go in, &amp; kill CT.  An Inny raid would probably have to clear most of the 2nd floor to get to Inny.  I'd like to see the 2nd floor treated as a completely separate area.  However, it might not be possible to do things on the 2nd floor without having them interefere with the first floor, and vice versa.<br>
<br>
Saying that the people that are 57+ can't kill CT/Inny because they didn't reserve fear is illogical.  We don't force those killing Trak to crawl Sebilis for 3 hours first.  We don't force Nagafen raiders to reserve FG's to kill Naggy.  Those who want to kill the Dain aren't forced to clear all of Kael first.<br>
<br>
Even though the name is the same on Inny &amp; CT, they're very different mobs.<br>
<br>
Bottom line.   People that are not capable of killing CT &amp; Inny shouldn't be preventing those that are from doing it.   <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune2.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukraghack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kraghack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 616<br> <font color=#CC9900>(3/20/01 1:03:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Discussion: Hate/Fear changes Re: Scheduling</span><hr size=1> <br>
